<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/285: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-23T11:00:00-04:00">May 23, 1938—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>75. Your 260, May 21, 6 p.m. We appreciate your suggestions as to any
                            step we could take which might be useful in the present crisis but after
                            consideration have decided that for the present at least a simultaneous
                            approach to Berlin and Praha would not be advisable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>